<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[264,1323,1716,1902]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis box="[264,390,1716,1741]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[935,1080,1716,1741]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Lomachaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[935,1080,1716,1741]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lomachaeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by lack of a distinct ventral mandibular tooth, distinctly brachyplumose setae, and by sparse, very small punctures on the pronotum and mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[735,823,1796,1822]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 13. 6 – 12" captionStartId="24.[264,382,1753,1777]" captionTargetBox="[324,1304,358,1675]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[256,1330,326,1729]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 13. 6 – 12, Pronotum and mesonotum of males, dorsal view of left half, not to same scale, 6. Lomachaeta chionothrix; 7. L. cirrhomeris; 8. L. hicksi; 9. L. hicksi; 10. L. hicksi; 11. L. hicksi; 12. L. ptilohyalus. 13. Mesonotum of L. hyphantria, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157430/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Fig. 
<number box="[790,823,1796,1822]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). It is most similar to 
<emphasis box="[1082,1253,1796,1821]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName box="[1082,1249,1796,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Lomachaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocopinna">L. crocopinna</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
especially regarding the presence of elongate setae on the parameres, but differs from this species by coloration of the metasoma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1323,284,1710]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis box="[312,578,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<typeStatus box="[312,419,284,309]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Holotype</typeStatus>
Male. Head.
</emphasis>
Width 
<quantity box="[670,779,284,310]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.92">0.92 mm</quantity>
, black, clothed throughout with sparse, long, erect, pale white setae. Compound eye maximum diameter 
<quantity box="[952,1060,324,350]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.37">0.37 mm</quantity>
. Median ocellus 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.9" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.069">0.069 mm</quantity>
, lateral ocellus 
<quantity box="[501,626,364,390]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.062">0.062 mm</quantity>
, ocellocular distance 
<quantity box="[884,993,364,390]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.27">0.27 mm</quantity>
, and interocellular distance 
<quantity box="[264,374,404,430]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
. Malar space very short, 
<quantity box="[682,790,404,430]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
in length. Mandible black except tip brown orange, slightly emarginate beneath, without distinct tooth beneath. Antennal tubercle brown. Antenna black. Scape clothed with pale white and black brachyplumose setae throughout. Pedicel and flagellomeres with decumbent white setae. Length of scape, pedicel and first three flagellomeres: 
<number box="[707,761,564,590]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="0.3">0.30</number>
, 
<number box="[774,843,564,590]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="0.092">0.092</number>
, 
<number box="[856,925,564,590]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="0.077">0.077</number>
, 
<number box="[938,989,564,590]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="0.12">0.12</number>
and 
<quantity box="[1049,1157,564,590]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
, respectively; width of first flagellomeres 
<quantity box="[595,719,604,630]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.799999999999999" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.088">0.088 mm</quantity>
; front with punctures small and dense; vertex with small, distinct, separated punctures and brown setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1323,284,1710]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis box="[312,437,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. Black brown. Clothed throughout with sparse, long, erect, pale white and black brown setae. Pronotum with small, distantly spaced punctures, not confluent on posterior margin. Mesonotum with small, distant punctures throughout. Scutellum almost flat, only very slightly convex, with small, shallow punctures similar to mesonotum but more crowded. Dorsum and posterior face of propodeum reticulate throughout. Tegula black with brown margin, glabrous, except entire margin punctate and with long, pale, erect setae. Legs brown, clothed with sparse, long, erect, brachyplumose pale white setae. Tibia and tarsus with golden bristles. Tibial spurs pale. Wings with pterostigma 
<quantity box="[1177,1286,964,990]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.17">0.17 mm</quantity>
in length along costa. Marginal cell 
<quantity box="[657,763,1004,1030]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.23">0.23 mm</quantity>
in length. Second submarginal cell pentagonal, 
<quantity box="[264,369,1044,1070]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.22">0.22 mm</quantity>
in length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1323,284,1710]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis box="[312,434,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Metasoma</emphasis>
. T 
<number box="[477,488,1084,1110]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
brown, orange laterally. Metasomal segment 
<number box="[1061,1075,1084,1110]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
and S 
<number box="[1161,1175,1084,1110]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0">3</number>
orange. T 
<number box="[1310,1323,1084,1110]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0">3</number>
orange, black brown medially. S 
<number box="[646,658,1124,1150]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
and metasomal segments 
<number box="[965,1010,1124,1150]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
brown. Metasoma clothed throughout with sparse, long, erect, pale white setae. T 
<number box="[901,914,1164,1190]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="5.0">5</number>
–T 
<number box="[949,963,1164,1190]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="7.0">7</number>
also with brown setae anterior to apical margin, denser on apical segments. Bristles at posterior margins of T 
<number box="[1195,1209,1204,1230]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
–T 
<number box="[1244,1259,1204,1230]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="4.0">4</number>
, pale orange. T 
<number box="[382,393,1244,1270]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
punctate on lateral margins, glabrous medially, posterior margin with row of small, contiguous punctures. T 
<number box="[634,648,1284,1310]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
with small, distant, widely separated punctures. T 
<number box="[1259,1272,1284,1310]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0">3</number>
–T 
<number box="[1306,1320,1284,1310]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="7.0">7</number>
with progressively small to fine, separated punctures. S 
<number box="[957,972,1324,1350]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
with large, close punctures throughout. Genitalia 
<figureCitation box="[522,608,1364,1390]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 23" captionStartId="25.[264,382,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[268,1316,324,1670]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[254,1331,306,1696]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 23. Internal view of male genitalia, 14. Lomachaeta chionothrix; 15. L. cirrhomeris; 16. L. hicksi; 17. L. hicksi; 18. L. hicksi; 19. L. ptilohyalus; 20. L. crocopinna; 21. L. hyphantria; 22. L. hicksi; 23. Smicromutilla beadugrimi; scale = 0.20 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157431/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number box="[576,608,1364,1390]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1323,284,1710]" box="[312,690,1404,1430]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis box="[312,393,1404,1429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Length</emphasis>
. Approximately 
<quantity box="[592,685,1404,1430]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="5.2">5.2 mm</quantity>
.
